MANHATTAN LIFE INS. CO., Appellant, v. ALEXANDER, Respondent. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. March 16, 1894.) Action by the Manhattan Life Insurance Company against Morris Alexander, impleaded.

Argued before VAN BRUNT, P. J., and O’BRIEN and PARKER, JJ.

Artemus H. Holmes, for appellant A. R. Dyett. for respondent.

No opinion. Judgment reversed and new trial ordered, with costs to appellant to abide event.
